President Biden has announced his intention to appoint Marilynn Malerba as Treasurer of the United States. If confirmed, Malerba, who is the Chief of the Mohegan Tribe, will become the first Native American to hold this position. As Treasurer, she will oversee important institutions such as the U.S. Mint, the Bureau of Engraving and Printing, and Fort Knox. She will also serve as a senior advisor to the Secretary of the Treasury in the areas of community development and public engagement. Malerba has a background in healthcare, having worked as a registered nurse and Director of Cardiology and Pulmonary Services at Lawrence & Memorial Hospital. She is currently a member of the Treasury Tribal Advisory Committee, which advises the Secretary of the Treasury on matters related to Native American finance.